ANTHRAX - UKRAINE (04): (ZAPORIZHIA) BOVINE, OIE
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 22 Aug 2012
Source: OIE [edited]
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=12218


Anthrax, Ukraine
----------------
Information received on 22 Aug 2012 from Dr Ivan Bisiuk, Head, State Committee for Veterinary Medicine, Ministry of Agricultural Policy, Kiev, Ukraine

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification (Final report)
Start date: 15 Aug 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 18 Aug 2012
Report date: 20 Aug 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Aug 2012
Date event resolved: 18 Aug 2012
Reason for notification: First occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks:
Outbreak 1: Voznesenka, Melitopol'skyi, Zaporozh'Ye
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Aug 2012
Outbreak status: Resolved (18 Aug 2012)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 25.00 percent / 25.00 percent / 100.00 percent / 25.00 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
* Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The cow was vaccinated more than a year ago.

Control measures:
Measures applied:
* Quarantine
* Movement control inside the country
* Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
Zaporozh'Ye / Sheep & goats / 117
Zaporozh'Ye / Cattle / 214
Zaporozh'Ye / Swine / 4
* Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
* No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied
* No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Zaporiz'ka Regional Laboratory of Veterinary Medicine (Local laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Ascoli test / 18 Aug 2012 / Positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 18 Aug 2012 / Positive
Cattle / optical microscopy / 18 Aug 2012 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations
Location of current outbreaks
[see OIE site for location]

